WEBVTT

00:04.571 --> 00:05.539 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.572 --> 00:06.540 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.573 --> 00:08.242 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And I'm Hari
Sreenivasan.

00:08.275 --> 00:10.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: On the "NewsHour"
tonight:
President-elect Donald Trump
appoints senior

00:10.777 --> 00:12.980 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
members of his economic team.

00:13.013 --> 00:18.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We look at who the men he wants
to run the
Treasury and Commerce
Departments are and

00:18.418 --> 00:20.220 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
what changes they may make.

00:20.254 --> 00:23.824 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Also ahead
this Wednesday,
former Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright

00:23.857 --> 00:28.428 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and former National Security
Adviser Stephen
Hadley are here to discuss the
future of the

00:28.462 --> 00:30.330 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Middle East under a Trump
presidency.

00:30.364 --> 00:36.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And bringing
Silicon Valley
to Salinas Valley -- how a poor
farming community

00:36.470 --> 00:40.407 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
in California is using
technology to revive
its economy.

00:40.440 --> 00:42.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PATRICK ZELAYA, Co-Founder,
HeavyConnect:
We believe that, when it comes
to ag-tech,

00:42.776 --> 00:46.313 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
if you can make it in the
Salinas Valley,
you're going to be able to have
a product

00:46.346 --> 00:47.681 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that will be adopted globally.

00:47.714 --> 00:50.684 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All that and
more on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:50.717 --> 00:54.955 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:54.988 --> 01:08.001 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: As the picture of
the Cabinet
president-elect Trump wants is
filled in,

01:08.035 --> 01:13.206 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we're seeing more figures who
reflect deep
ties to Washington or Wall
Street.

01:13.240 --> 01:18.779 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It's a contrast with his
campaign, during
which he disparaged the power
centers as corrupt

01:18.812 --> 01:21.682 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and out of touch with ordinary
Americans.

01:21.715 --> 01:23.483 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Lisa Desjardins has our report.

01:23.517 --> 01:27.120 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Two fronts for
the transition
of power today.

01:27.154 --> 01:31.725 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In Washington, vice
president-elect Mike Pence
worked on alliances with
Republican leaders

01:31.758 --> 01:37.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on Capitol Hill, as, in New
York, team Trump
offered more Cabinet nominees
for Congress

01:37.497 --> 01:43.570 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to consider, including the
highest ranking
yet, financier Steven Mnuchin
for treasury

01:43.603 --> 01:45.372 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
secretary.

01:45.405 --> 01:46.239 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
STEVE MNUCHIN, Treasury
Secretary Nominee:
I couldn't be more excited about
the opportunity

01:46.273 --> 01:48.075 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to work with him in the
administration.

01:48.108 --> 01:54.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And our number one priority is
going to be
the economy, get back to 3 to 4
percent growth.

01:54.314 --> 01:56.783 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We believe that's very
sustainable.

01:56.817 --> 01:58.952 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And focus on things for the
American worker.

01:58.986 --> 02:00.754 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's absolutely our priority.

02:00.787 --> 02:05.625 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Mnuchin's
resume is full
of Wall Street experience,
including 17 years

02:05.659 --> 02:07.227 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
at Goldman Sachs.

02:07.260 --> 02:09.730 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He has no government experience.

02:09.763 --> 02:14.134 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
During the election, he headed
up fund-raising
operations for the Trump
campaign, and had

02:14.167 --> 02:18.271 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a hand in shaping candidate
Trump's message
on taxes.

02:18.305 --> 02:23.143 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If confirmed, he'd be tasked
with turning
that rhetoric into reality.

02:23.176 --> 02:28.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Alongside him this morning on
CNBC, billionaire
investor Wilbur Ross, who is Mr.
Trump's pick

02:28.782 --> 02:32.786 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to be the commerce secretary and
a point person
on trade policy.

02:32.819 --> 02:36.123 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILBUR ROSS, Commerce Secretary
Nominee: The
real trick is going to be
increase American

02:36.156 --> 02:37.691 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
exports.

02:37.724 --> 02:42.095 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Get rid of some of the tariff
and non-tariff
barriers to American exports.

02:42.129 --> 02:46.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Ross is known
for turning
around troubled companies, where
he cuts costs

02:46.533 --> 02:49.736 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and sometimes worker benefits to
boost profits.

02:49.770 --> 02:56.209 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He also owned the Sago coal mine
in West Virginia,
where a collapse killed 12
miners in 2006.

02:56.243 --> 02:59.679 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He said, "It was the worst week
of my entire
life."

02:59.713 --> 03:05.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mr. Trump also picked out a
deputy for Ross,
Chicago Cubs co-owner Todd
Ricketts, a prominent

03:05.552 --> 03:11.658 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Republican donor who, at one
point in the
campaign, spoke out against
candidate Trump.

03:11.691 --> 03:14.461 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Mr. Trump made other jobs news
today, too.

03:14.494 --> 03:18.865 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Overnight, there was word that
he had cut
a deal with the air conditioner
maker Carrier

03:18.899 --> 03:21.968 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to keep 1,000 jobs in Indiana.

03:22.002 --> 03:26.940 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That is most, but not all of the
jobs that
the company said it was going to
eliminate.

03:26.973 --> 03:31.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also today, there were questions
about Mr.
Trump's own business future when
he's president.

03:31.445 --> 03:36.950 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On Twitter, he said he would
take himself
-- quote -- "completely out of
business operations,"

03:36.983 --> 03:41.488 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and indicated he will explain
how in a news
conference in two weeks.

03:41.521 --> 03:45.358 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Also still unknown, who will be
Mr. Trump's
secretary of state.

03:45.392 --> 03:49.596 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president-elect met a second
time with
one candidate, Mitt Romney, last
night in

03:49.629 --> 03:50.797 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
New York.

03:50.831 --> 03:54.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Afterwards, Mr. Trump's former
critic had
warm words.

03:54.034 --> 03:58.205 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MITT ROMNEY (R), Former
Presidential Candidate:
These discussions I have had
with him have

03:58.238 --> 04:00.006 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
been enlightening, and
interesting, and engaging.

04:00.040 --> 04:02.075 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I have enjoyed them very, very
much.

04:02.109 --> 04:07.380 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: All this as
Green Party candidate
Jill Stein officially filed a
hand recount

04:07.414 --> 04:12.252 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
request in Michigan, the third
of three states
she has pledged to verify.

04:12.285 --> 04:14.421 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm Lisa
Desjardins.

04:14.454 --> 04:19.726 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And we will have
more on president-elect
Trump's picks right after our
news summary.

04:19.759 --> 04:23.430 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: In the day's
other news:
The North Carolina police
officer who fatally

04:23.463 --> 04:26.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
shot a black man in September
will not face
criminal charges.

04:26.933 --> 04:31.071 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The shooting of Keith Lamont
Scott, whose
family at first insisted he
wasn't armed,

04:31.104 --> 04:33.406 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
sparked days of protests across
Charlotte.

04:33.440 --> 04:37.544 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, the county prosecutor
said there was
evidence Scott was holding a
gun, and ignored

04:37.577 --> 04:39.379 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
repeated requests to drop it.

04:39.412 --> 04:42.215 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
ANDREW MURRAY, District
Attorney: The central
issue is whether Officer Vinson
was lawful

04:42.249 --> 04:45.485 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in using deadly force against
Mr. Scott.

04:45.519 --> 04:49.189 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Anyone is justified in using
deadly force
if he reasonably believed, and,
in fact, believed

04:49.222 --> 04:54.561 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that he or someone else was in
imminent danger
of great bodily injury or death.

04:54.594 --> 04:58.431 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Scott's family
insisted
today's decision will not end
their inquiry.

04:58.465 --> 05:03.103 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The death toll
from the wildfires
that swept through Tennessee's
Great Smoky

05:03.136 --> 05:05.739 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Mountains rose to seven today.

05:05.772 --> 05:11.178 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Dozens of people have been
injured and more
than 700 buildings were damaged
or destroyed.

05:11.211 --> 05:16.550 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Heavy rain brought some relief
today, but,
at points, more than 200
firefighters were

05:16.583 --> 05:18.285 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
still fighting the flames.

05:18.318 --> 05:22.923 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GREG MILLER, Gatlinburg,
Tennessee, Fire Chief:
We have all seen how fires
rekindle.

05:22.956 --> 05:27.460 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And whatever rain we got, and
these structures
may dry out and they could start
back.

05:27.494 --> 05:30.730 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But we have crews that are
monitoring those
and going back in those areas.

05:30.764 --> 05:34.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They are driving through and
they're checking
and looking for hot spots.

05:34.100 --> 05:38.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Officials are
still investigating
what started the fires, but they
believe they

05:38.805 --> 05:40.674 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
were likely caused by humans.

05:40.707 --> 05:44.911 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Powerful
storms soaked the
tinder-dry South overnight,
spawning tornadoes

05:44.945 --> 05:46.846 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that left five people dead.

05:46.880 --> 05:51.418 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The twisters tore through
Northeastern Alabama,
damaging buildings and killing
three people.

05:51.451 --> 05:55.322 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Across the border in Southern
Tennessee, two
others died, and dozens more
were injured.

05:55.355 --> 05:59.759 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some roads in the South were
drenched with
up to two feet of water, after
two months

05:59.793 --> 06:01.561 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
without rain.

06:01.595 --> 06:04.831 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: There is word
today that the
pilot of the charter plane that
slammed into

06:04.864 --> 06:10.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Colombia's Andes Mountains told
air traffic
controllers that he ran out of
fuel moments

06:10.971 --> 06:12.439 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
before the crash.

06:12.472 --> 06:16.276 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That is according to a leaked
recording of
the flight's final minutes.

06:16.309 --> 06:19.913 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
All but six of the 77 people on
board died.

06:19.946 --> 06:22.148 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Most were members of a Brazilian
soccer team.

06:22.182 --> 06:26.419 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: In Syria,
opposition activists
claimed nearly 50 civilians were
killed by

06:26.453 --> 06:31.258 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
regime forces today as they fled
rebel-held
Eastern Aleppo.

06:31.291 --> 06:33.393 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Most of the victims were women
and children.

06:33.426 --> 06:37.931 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Activists estimate more than
50,000 people
have been displaced by the
fighting in the

06:37.964 --> 06:39.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
past four days.

06:39.766 --> 06:44.271 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The director of
the CIA has
decried president-elect Donald
Trump's plan

06:44.304 --> 06:47.307 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to scrap the nuclear deal with
Iran.

06:47.340 --> 06:52.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a BBC interview, John Brennan
said -- quote
-- "I think it would be
disastrous.

06:52.379 --> 06:56.916 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think it would be the height
of folly if
the next administration were to
tear up that

06:56.950 --> 06:58.718 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
agreement."

06:58.752 --> 07:02.922 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Brennan argued such a move would
open the
door for still other countries
to pursue nuclear

07:02.956 --> 07:04.724 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
weapons.

07:04.758 --> 07:07.160 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The United
Nations Security
Council slapped new sanctions on
North Korea

07:07.193 --> 07:12.232 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
today, in response to its fifth,
and largest,
nuclear test in September.

07:12.265 --> 07:15.902 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The council unanimously approved
the resolution,
which will slash North Korea's
biggest export,

07:15.935 --> 07:18.471 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
coal, by at least 62 percent.

07:18.505 --> 07:22.909 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It also bans the regime from
exporting metals
like copper, nickel, and silver.

07:22.942 --> 07:27.213 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Democrats in the
U.S. House
of Representatives reelected
California's

07:27.247 --> 07:29.783 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Nancy Pelosi as their leader
today.

07:29.816 --> 07:33.353 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The congresswoman has led the
party in the
House since 2002.

07:33.386 --> 07:41.494 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Pelosi survived a challenge from
Ohio Representative
Tim Ryan in a 134-63 vote.

07:41.528 --> 07:46.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Her win came despite
disenchantment from some
in her caucus after a
disappointing showing

07:46.766 --> 07:47.734 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in this month's elections.

07:47.767 --> 07:49.502 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

07:49.536 --> 07:53.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NANCY PELOSI (D-CA), House
Minority Leader:
We have a responsibility, and we
embrace the

07:53.073 --> 07:56.376 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
opportunity that is presented.

07:56.409 --> 07:57.677 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We know how to win elections.

07:57.711 --> 07:58.978 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We have done it in the past.

07:59.012 --> 08:01.047 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We will do it again.

08:01.081 --> 08:06.386 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Maryland
Congressman Steny
Hoyer was also reelected as
House Democratic

08:06.419 --> 08:08.288 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
whip.

08:08.321 --> 08:11.858 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The oil cartel
OPEC is decreasing
oil production for the first
time in eight

08:11.891 --> 08:13.660 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
years.

08:13.693 --> 08:16.429 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Member nations agreed to a deal
that will
cut production by more than a
million barrels

08:16.463 --> 08:21.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a day, from its current daily
output of over
33 million barrels.

08:21.034 --> 08:23.970 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's all part of an effort to
boost lagging
oil prices.

08:24.003 --> 08:28.675 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: That news sent
energy stocks
soaring on Wall Street today,
but markets

08:28.708 --> 08:30.176 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ended the day mixed.

08:30.210 --> 08:35.815 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
gained two
points to close at 19123.

08:35.849 --> 08:40.687 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Nasdaq tumbled 56, and the
S&amp;P 500 slipped
nearly six.

08:40.720 --> 08:48.361 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
the men who
will shape Trump's economic
agenda; on the

08:48.395 --> 08:53.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ground in a rapidly changing
Cuba; Madeleine
Albright and Stephen Hadley on
what to do

08:53.900 --> 09:01.808 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
next in the Mideast; and much
more.

09:01.841 --> 09:12.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, as we have been reporting,
the president-elect
began fleshing out his economic
team today

09:12.385 --> 09:16.689 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by announcing his choices to run
the Departments
of Treasury and Commerce.

09:16.723 --> 09:22.095 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In doing so, the candidate, who
campaigned
with a heavy dose of populism,
elevated individuals

09:22.128 --> 09:26.299 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
mainly known for their
connections to Wall
Street and high finance.

09:26.332 --> 09:30.603 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
David Wessel of the Brookings
Institution
and a contributing columnist to
The Wall Street

09:30.637 --> 09:32.238 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Journal joins me now.

09:32.272 --> 09:34.174 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And welcome back to the program.

09:34.207 --> 09:36.009 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID WESSEL, The Wall Street
Journal: Thank
you.

09:36.042 --> 09:38.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, David, fill
out this picture
a little bit more of who --
let's start with

09:38.344 --> 09:39.679 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Steve Mnuchin.

09:39.712 --> 09:42.849 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's the pick to head the
Treasury Department.

09:42.882 --> 09:44.684 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
